==== Mother ====
By 1978 a group of people centered around a female member, one Um Sooin{{efn|{{lang-ko|엄수인|links=no}}; {{transl|ko|''eom-su-in''}}{{r|uakfv}}}} (born 1941), within the Witnesses of Jesus Church of God, claimed through a chain of scriptural [[eisegesis]] that they published in writing, that Um variously was "the only [[Bride of Christ|bride]]", "the [[New Jerusalem|Heavenly Jerusalem]]", "the [[New Jerusalem]]" on earth, "the [[The Paraclete|comforter]] sent by God", and they asserted that she was "our [[Heavenly Mother|mother]] who has come down from Heaven", and that Ahn was [[Christ]].{{r|kchr130528}}{{r|enjerusalem}}{{r|kojerusalem}} Um and the group around her claiming she was the spiritual mother were expelled from the church,{{r|kcourt2005}}{{r|enjerusalem}}{{r|kojerusalem}} and Ahn dedicated a book entitled ''[http://ncpcog.co.kr/rb/home/b/0604/441 Problems with the New Jerusalem, the Bride and Women's Veils]'' (1980, reprinted 1983) to the controversy, in which he writes:
{{Quote box
| title = 
| quote = This booklet was published to prevent troublemakers who misinterpret and behave fanatically, [and] explain the errors in the books that Um Sooin published ... women like Um Sooin have caused a great problem to arise with her corrupt ideas ... The Jerusalem in Heaven is Our Mother ... Um Sooin speaks as if she is out of her mind when she claims that the [[New Jerusalem]] is herself ... they assert that Um Sooin is our mother who has come down from Heaven. ... How extremely scandalous is this? With this type of misguided [[delusion]], she has become a [[false prophet]] and has attempted to gain power. ... The New Jerusalem which is written of in {{bibleref2|REV|21:1-4|NIV|Revelation 21:1-4}} ... is a spiritual building not a person. .... Nobody except someone who is not in their right state of mind can believe and follow after this. ... Because the interpretation of Um Sooin was made to match their claims, they have made these ridiculous interpretations. ...
| align = center |width = 60% |border = |fontsize = |bgcolor = |style = |title_bg = |title_fnt = |tstyle = |qalign = |qstyle = |quoted = 
{{hidden end}}
| salign = right
| source = <small>Ahn Sahng-hong, ''Problems with the New Jerusalem, the Bride and Women's Veils'', 1980 & 1983</small>{{r|enjerusalem}}{{r|kojerusalem}}
}}
Ahn concludes his rebuking of Um Sooin:
{{Quote box
| title = 
| quote = There is never a time when the activity of [[Satan]] is cut off in the true Church. The [[Paul the Apostle|Apostle Paul]] has written as follows that the [[Devil]] will utilize women to cause confusion inside the Church:
"A woman should learn in quietness and full submission. I do not permit a woman to teach or to assume authority over a man; she must be quiet. For Adam was formed first, then Eve. And Adam was not the one deceived; it was the woman who was deceived and became a sinner."{{bibleref2c|1TIM|2:11-14|NIV|1 Timothy 2:11-14}}
In other words, whenever a woman makes assertions in the Church, the Church will fall under the deception of the Devil.
