'''Khalikawe''' or '''Kalikawe''' is a name or symbol which means "[[Religious belief|believer]]". It usually refers to being [[succession (disambiguation)|successor]] of your life, but is also used as a symbol among the Nilo-Saharan [[Islamic]] religious groups pronounced and written as "'''خالقالكونرعب'''".{{Clarify|date=July 2017}}


== Concept Lived person ==
* [[Bongoland]]{{Clarify|date=July 2017}}
* In both [[Bantu peoples|Buntu Tribes]] and [[Nilo-Saharan languages|Nilo-Saharan Tribes]] a Khalikawe is a [[Believer's baptism|spiritual believer]] of a life successor which in [[Swahili language|Swahili]] means mrithi.{{Clarify|date=July 2017}}

== Origin ==
Khalikawe is originated from the [[Great Mosque of Kilwa]].{{Clarify|date=July 2017}}

